statement: F. 000001time limit per test1 secondmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstdinoutputstdoutInputThe input contains a single integera(1 ≤a≤ 64).OutputOutput a single integer.ExamplesInput2Output1Input4Output2Input27Output5Input42Output6

processed.result: You are given an integer $a$ ($1 \le a \le 64$). Output the smallest integer $b$ such that $b$ is greater than $a$ and $b$ has at least one '1' bit in its binary representation.
Given a number, output the number of digits it has.
